- Namespace wraps the global system resource into an abstraction.
- Namespace creates **isolated instance** of that global resource and the resource is only accessible within that namespace.
- pid namespace - provides dedicated space for process IDs, ensuring that container processes remain unware of any external processes.
- net namespace - isolates network stack, giving each container its own networking environment.
- mnt namespace - provide distict file system hierarchy, shielding container from the host's filesystem structure.
- uts namespace - allowing containers to have thier own hostname and domain name. independent of the host system.
- ips namespace - safeguard inter-process communication resources, preventing inteference between containers.
- user namespace - ensuring isolation of user & group IDS, allowing secure mapping between container & host identities. Docker does not enable the user namespace bydefault.
	
	
	
